synopsis_with_character_names:
"Graceland" - "Smoke Alarm" - August 15, 2013

Mike runs on the beach. He is frustrated.

Briggs tosses in bed. He is in pain. He puts an icepack on the ribs that Mike bruised/broke.

Johnny showers. Charlie brushes her teeth. They joke around in the bathroom. She admits her curiosit about Briggs is not yet satisfied. She says lack of evidence doesn't equal innocence.

Paige, who was surfing, chats with Mike on the beach. He is sad about Abby.

They all convene in the kitchen for breakfast, Johnny cooks "ghetto scramble."

Mike says all is quiet on the Bello/Caza cartel front for the moment. Briggs says it won't be for long because "Jangles" will soon be showing up. Charlie wants to move on Odin. Briggs says he's a ghost and doesn't want to waste energy on the hunt.

Mike gets a call. It turns out that Jangles killed one of Bello's corner dealers and hung his shoes from telephone wire. The shoes still have the dealer's feet in them.

Briggs sits on the beach and makes a call to a Diane hotel and arranges for keys to be let in a planter there for him so he can make a "discreet" entrance. He picks them up and enters the hotel later that night. He hangs up a smoke detector surveillance system. He heads back to Graceland enjoys some tea and looks at the empty room all night.

Mike drives to meet Bello at his fancy safe house. His team has ears on him through his watch. They share a cigar. Mike says he seems happy. Bello says he's not scared by the feet on the wire. He says he's seen worse and has some henchmen bring out "the case. The case is full of automatic weapons.

Charlie is chatting with a source who tells her Federales got a hit on a Mexican shell company with ties to Odin Rossi. Money was taken from the account to get a hotel room. She thinks she can find Odin in the room. (Which is obviously the room that Briggs is surveilling.)

Bello hands out the high powered firearms to his crew. It is supposed to make them look like a "deterrent." Mike is supposed to train them.

Back at Graceland Mike and Briggs talk about Bello and Mike says he wants to go to the FBI and bring Bello in. He feels guilty that when bullets start flying on the streets he will have trained the people shooting. Briggs says they have to wait, to catch one monster in order to get another, in this case Jangles, and Odin. Briggs wants justice just like Mike. Mike wonders if he really wants vengeance. Briggs says he wants both and closure.

Mike goes to Juan and asks why Briggs is still in the field since he said he was going to get help. Juan says there's more work to be done and to keep on it and he thinks Briggs is connected to the Caza cartel and probably wants to sell Bello out. Juan says sometimes it's about using one monster as bait to catch another monster, echoing exactly what Briggs said. Mike immediately backs off when hearing this. He heads home, finds the picture Juan gave him of his grandfather's crime scene photo, smashes it and underneath the picture finds a bug. Paige comes in because she heard the frame smashing. He said the frame "fell." As she helps him with a Band-Aid she says her BS detector is going off and she had hoped that he trusted her enough to help him. He says he does trust her but it's complicated. He says she wouldn't understand. She says she's trying to. He still clams up. She says to keep doing what he's doing because it's clearly working out.

Charlie cases the Diane Motel where Briggs is staying. She breaks into a room. Briggs watches. He exclaims "shit" when he sees her walk in. She looks through the room. She sees the camera with which he is watching her. It's hidden in a smoke detector. She pulls it off the wall. As she's leaving a man enters gun drawn. She pulls her gun. He shows his Federales badge, Rafael Cortez. He says he pictured Odin Rossi being a woman. She says she pictured him looking like Rafael Cortez. She shows her FBI badge. He is the Federales who got the tip about the money from the Mexican shell company being used to get the room. He followed her in because he was also casing the joint. He suggests working together, pooling their resources, since Odin has given them very little to go on. She says she'll have to think about it. (So Briggs used the money on purpose to draw out the Federales but didn't plan on it tipping off Charlie. But he did not see their conversation.)

Mike confronts Juan with the bug from his room. He asks if he told Briggs about their investigation. He was afraid he was losing Mike to Briggs. Mike asks why Juan is so fixated on Briggs since he's never even met him. Juan levels with him that Graceland isn't the first of its kind, that Briggs worked in a house called Estate. Juan knew Briggs' training officer Roberto, they were friends at Quantico. His friend and four other agents died in a house fire in the Estate. Badillo thinks he was turned by Caza cartel and burned down the house and killed his friend and the others. Mike says they have no proof to tie Briggs to the fire. Nine hours earlier a call from a payphone came to the house and then later to a girl in the house Briggs was seeing. Juan starts getting a little unhinged and says that Mike is going to help him get Briggs. Mike says he isn't and walks out.

Briggs and Johnny chat at the house. He asks if there's something "up" with Charlie. Johnny says she's not over Whistler and the stuff that happened between them at the house. He admits that Charlie thinks something's up between him and Odin. He acts surprised. He switches gears to talk about trying to catch Jangles and asks if Johnny can help. Johnny thinks he can.

They go to a divey bar. They chat with the pretty bartender. Johnny's really into her but she's not allowed to date "bangers" and notes that he'd have more luck with his actual badge. Briggs wants info. But Johnny tells him to be patient. Johnny asks her about the "chopped off feet." She says she heard people joking about it and points one out in the bar at the moment. Briggs goes to check it out.

Charlie does research on Cortez.

Mike delivers Chinese food to Bello. Bello asks what the mood is out there. Mike says his men are scared. Bello thinks this is good. Mike says the Caza cartel isn't after him but Odin and he wonders why he doesn't just sell him out. Bello says this is a war and beating Caza is worth it, it buys him independence. Mike points out that his men are going to die. Bello says no more talking and no more deals. He says that the lives of his men mean something to him and he doesn't take joy from their bloodshed. He says Mike taught the men to shoot the enemy and they will be fine and they toast that they shared victory will be sweet.

Johnny continues to chat with the bartender and tells her he's thinking about joining the LAPD but she can't tell anyone. Briggs returns to the bar and says the guys in the booth include one of Bello's guys selling them out on where Bello's safe house is. They scramble to tell Mike and assemble a team.

Bello and Mike jaw about the great combo of Chinese food and cigars like Butch and Sundance. Bello objects to their quippiness and the "Raindrops Keep Fallin' on My Head" song. Suddenly the sprinklers go off.

Mike goes to shut them of and one of Bello's men is dead. he calls for back-up.

Briggs drives and tries to make a call but no one is picking up. He comes upon Mike's back-up crew that he just called for back-up and they're all dead. Briggs runs with his gun. We cut to Bello being torture by Jangles. Jangles asks where Odin Rossi is. Bello refuses to help. Mike's shoe squeaks and Jangles hears. A shootout ensues but Mike can't hit Jangles. He tells Bello to run. Jangles stabs Mike. Briggs arrives and shoots at him and misses. He goes to Mike who tells him to go after Jangles. Briggs says "next time." He applies pressure on the wound until back-up shows up. Bello is led out in cuffs. Mike makes the FBI guys read him his rights in front of Bello. Then he passes out. Briggs can't catch up with Jangles.

Mike wakes up in a hotel room. Hazy. Paige is there. She says the doctor says he will need time to get better. He asks if there are any gifts from the FBI or an anonymous source. She asks what's going on. He says they all lie for the job and that they can walk in Graceland and be themselves but he can't because he was placed in Graceland to investigate Briggs. She accuses him of being a "rat." She said he could trust her and now that he's spilling she abandons him.

Juan sits in the car and listens to surveillance from Mike's room of him and Briggs talking and of Briggs saying he never saw Jangles because he always wore a bandanda. Juan puts on a bandanna and looks in the rear-view mirror.

Charlie meets with Rafael Cortez at a diner. (Looking at his hair now, I'm guessing he's "Jangles.") He congratulates her on the FBI taking down Bello. She asks what the rumor is on his side. He said the police thinks the Caza are escorting Jangles back to Mexico but he says he guarantees he's still around. Charlie says she will work Odin out of Bello. She talks about them working together. He loves this idea. We pull back and see e blood marks on his jacket.

Briggs is drunk on the beach by a bonfire. He looks at a charm and remembers the agent Lisa that he loved in the Estate. Juan Badillo is in his car and reports into a tape recorder that he is about to approach Briggs and that he is undercover as the Caza mercenary known as Jangles. Briggs cries on the beach and pound the sand. Juan approaches. he says "you're looking for me right?" Briggs asks if he knows what this place is? Jangles says he does and that Briggs killed everyone here. Briggs says they both did and that Jangles lit the match by making him a junkie. Juan pulls a gun which confuses Briggs since Jangles didn't use guns. They struggle and the gun goes off and Juan is dead.

description: Tempers flare and relationships are pushed to the brink when Charlie discovers a secret about Briggs and begins working with a Federale to find the truth. Mike discovers that Juan is missing and that the FBI has a suspect: Paul Briggs.

synopsis_with_character_names:
"Graceland" - "King's Castle" - August 22, 2013

We open where we left off, a drunk Briggs on the beach contemplating the fact that he just shot Juan Badillo, who he thinks was his Caza cartel tormentor "Jangles."

We flashback to a year and a half ago. The gang was playing darts at the bar with the old agent Donnie who still lived in the house. They were talking about another agent who was being brought up on manslaughter charges for killing a suspect while on drugs. Johnny was new to the house at that point. Briggs says one too many drinks or pills can mean the difference between a medal and a murder rap.

We come back to the present. Briggs rolls the body up in a tarp, goes over the scene, and heads out. We see that Badillo's car is in the distance with a tape recorder in it rolling. Briggs takes Badillo to a remote desert location and buries the body. He notices on the keychain a key that says "Apt. 3."

Bello is in custody trying to cut a deal. He wants immunity for giving up on Odin Rossi. Charlie tries to scare him by saying the Caza cartel members in jail will repeatedly shank and rape him in prison and if he gives up Rossi they can put him in protective custody. He wants immunity, period.

Mike returns to the house a few days earlier, having checked out against medical advice. He is still clearly hurting.

Johnny is trying to plan a surprise party for Jakes. Jakes hates surprise parties which is why he's doing it. He has decided on a bounce house and strippers. No one is up for helping him though. Paige is out when she sees Mike is back. Charlie is pre-occupied with Bello and Briggs is MIA.

The next morning at breakfast Jakes warns Johnny not to throw him a party.

Charlie meets with her Federale contact Cortez (aka Jangles.) They both say they have nothing: he has nothing on Jangles, she has nothing on Odin Rossi. The Federale says Bello must have a weakness, someone or something he cares about. Charlie gets an idea.

Briggs tells Mike to count his sutures as a badge of honor. Charlie heads home with her plan: she wants Mike to go undercover in prison with Bello, thinking Bello will give up Odin to protect Mike. Briggs argues against it vehemently, under the guise of it being bad for Mike, not protect his identity as Odin. Mike says he's in.

Mike orange suits up and meets with Bello in the prison yard. He tells Mike that maybe he can do something.

Jakes sneaks into Johnny's room and sees the brochure for the bounce house and cancels it but says to charge his card anyway. Johnny overhears and re-orders it.

Briggs finds Charlie in Mike's room looking through his drawers. She says the banged up frame with his grandfather's photo. She tells him she was looking for Mike's meds to bring to him in jail. She tells him she's going right when visitation starts. Briggs gets an idea: he calls the prison and sets up a visitation with Bello--right when it starts. Bello knows who Charlie is.

The next morning when he comes into the visiting room he sees Mike talking to her and realizes he's a Fed. He attacks the already injured Mike and pummels him before the guards can pull him off. He screams at Mike: "I trusted you!"

Charlie brings the injured Mike home--where Johnny is still trying to get Paige excited for Jakes' party. Charlie is livid and calls Briggs on the carpet. She tells him what happened and that it had to be an Odin thing since no one showed up for the visitation. Mike gets a call to come into the bureau right then, everyone thinks he's getting a commendation.

It is not a commendation. The director Clark tells him that Badillo is missing and they think that Briggs has something to do with it. Clark has in his possession a little essay Mike wrote when he was 9 years old where he talks about wanting to be an FBI agent and that it's all about truth and justice. He wants Mike to keep looking into Briggs. Mike says he will but he's confused because as far as he knows Briggs didn't even know Badillo. Clark says they can't find his car but think Badillo was probably recording so when they find it it will be helpful.

Johnny is busy blowing up the bounce house in the living room and welcoming strippers to the house. Charlie is going over the detention center's incoming calls to isolate who called in the visitation to Bello. Briggs notes she's doing it right in front of everyone instead of upstairs. She says she was hoping to inspire him to help her. When he declines she storms upstairs.

Mike returns home and Paige pulls him aside to talk. Briggs and Johnny think they're having a "lover's quarrel."

Paige is still angry. Mike explains what happens and tells her about Briggs being a junkie and the Juan Badillo stuff. She tells him to tell Briggs about the investigation and that he isn't a murderer. They talk, he wonders aloud if that's a good idea, but asks "what if we're wrong?"

Jakes is busy spending his birthday in the bar talking to Derek, the man now living with his ex-girlfriend Cassie and son Daniel. They talk a bit. Derek admits he's having trouble with Cassie and is spending the night in a motel. Jakes admits that he used to have a family and he walked away from it. They both tell each other to fight for what they want. Knowing that Derek is out at the motel, Jakes goes to Cassie's at 3 am, drunk, pounds on the door and essentially begs to take him back. He lets slip that he talked to Derek and she is officially done with him.

When he returns home, he finds only Johnny and one of the strippers. He hauls off and slugs Johnny, needing to hit someone. They fight. Johnny is legitimately hurt that Jakes doesn't seem to care about him. Johnny notes that he has nothing else.. Jakes stumbles to his room. Johnny goes upstairs and stands in the hallway in the middle of the rooms and unloads. He yells at all the closed doors, behind which all the inhabitants are awake, that they are a family whether they like it or not. And given that they spend so much time cozying up to drug dealers and low life's the fact that he wants to blow off some steam and forget about all that dark stuff for one night with his friends/family shouldn't be too much to ask.

Mike visits Bello in prison. Bello basically calls him on the fact that he was also a drug dealer and complicit in torture and death, especially with regards to Eddie. Bello tells him that at least he is paying for his sins, unlike Mike.

Mike confesses to Briggs about his investigation. Briggs isn't surprised. Mike essentially says he trusts him and is on his side and he tells him about Badillo being missing. Briggs, truthfully, says he's never heard of Badillo. Mike says he's going to find Badillo's car and wants Briggs to help. Briggs says that would look bad, like a cover-up. Mike agrees and then apologizes. Briggs looks both pleased and worried.

Charlie meets with the Federale/Jangles and brings the surveillance devices she found in the Diane Motel. She posits the theory that Odin is a federal agent. She says she doesn't have a name but it seems clear she thinks it's Briggs. He says when she has a name, he'll help. She says they're in the hunt together. He asks how they should proceed.

Mike tells Paige he told him. She wonders why. She says to see his face when he said Badillo's name. Mike says he had no idea who he was.

Briggs looks up Badillo in the FBI database and realizes he's in a world of trouble.

description: Looking for the truth about Juan's disappearance, Briggs and Mike play a dangerous game of cat and mouse- forcing Briggs to make a major decision about his future.
tags: ['false identity', 'knife', 'father figure', 'contraband']
synopsis_with_character_names:
"Graceland" - "Happy Endings" - Sept. 5, 2013

Briggs lies in bed in contemplation at 2:30 a.m. He hops on his laptop and looks at the "missing" poster for Juan Badillo. He notes the address and heads out. In the living room he chats with Mike who's pretending to be asleep Briggs goes back to the kitchen and abandons his plan to leave. For now.

He goes to Jakes and wakes him up and asks for his help, calling in a favor he owes him. He says he needs a car to disappear across the border in the way only a customs agent knows how. But not now, tomorrow.

Mike and Paige put a tracker on Briggs' car. They both feel bad but still do it.

Johnny makes shaped pancakes. He won't make a special one for Jakes. He asks for help on closing down his bird smuggling operation. Briggs volunteers. Mike asks about Badillo and Briggs says he's staying far away and that if anyone can find the car it's Mike. He heads out with Jakes and they take his car, thus avoiding the tracker.

Mike watches the tracker and there's no movement and realize they took Jakes' truck. Paige tells them to focus on what they can control and that's finding Juan's car.

Turns out Jakes wasn't lying about the birds, it wasn't just an alibi. Jakes tells Briggs about running into Cassandra and how bad it went and that's why it went down with Johnny. And that Johnny will get over it. Briggs tells Jakes to let her go, since it's impossible with the job.

Charlie and Rafael dress to meet. He also gets his "Jangles" doctor bag and keys ready to go.

Charlie and Johnny argue about how she ruined the bouncy house. They then argue about how no one is helping with her case against Odin.

Jakes and Briggs head to look for the car. Briggs says he needs to get something from the car. They think it got jacked.

Simultaneously, Paige and Mike find the guy who jacked it online at a gas station surveillance camera in Long Beach.

Charlie and Cortez meet at a bar and talk about their respective quests: her for Odin and him for "Jangles" -- which is of course him. He asks if anyone knows she's working with him. She says no. He says maybe he can track Odin, who she thinks is an FBI agent and she doesn't want to give up his name yet.

Jakes and Briggs keep looking for the car, thinking a gangbanger took it. Briggs gets very upset and pounds the dashboard. Jakes pulls over and asks him what's really up, "what's in the car?" He admits it's a recording. Jakes demands more answers. Briggs tells him he killed an FBI agent. He explains the whole scenario, Jangles, the struggle, the gun. He thought he'd gotten Jangles but it was an FBI agent Juan Badillo who wanted him to incriminate himself with the Caza cartel. Jakes can't believe it but says he will help.

Briggs and Charlie head to a hotel room and she's drunk and Jangles wants to do her in, but Johnny calls her just as they're going in. Charlie says they have to take a raincheck. Jangles is not happy.

Mike and Paige go to church to speak to the mother of the guy who jacked the car. She wouldn't talk to FBI agents so they pretend she is pregnant and hope to appeal to her motherly side. She asks to find him but the mother is bitchy and rude shuts her down and thinks she's trashy. But she gives up the address.

Just then Briggs and Jakes show up at the guy's front, a donut shop. Briggs brings in one of the exotic birds as a gift. Clayton, the smash and grab guy, is grateful for the bird for his evil mom. Briggs claims that he's looking for work, says he's trying to get a girl back quickly. Clayton says he has a job but needs two guys. he calls in Jakes.

Paige and Mike show up at the donut shop and see Jakes in the truck. He tells him Briggs is inside. Just then Briggs' texts him to come in. Instead Mike walks in. Briggs is shocked to say the least but he covers. Clayton gives them a smash and grab job for the next day. They walk out and argue, Briggs claims he was lying and of course he's looking for the car. He lies again and says he never heard of the guy. Briggs says clearly Mike has doubts too. Mike says he'll believe what he hears on the tape in Juan's car.

Charlie and Johnny figure out how to work on Quinn, the evil drug dealer who worked for Odin. She normally worked with Briggs but since she thinks Briggs is Odin, she can't do that so she tells Johnny she's going to work with "another" partner but won't tell him Cortez' name.

Paige and Mike mull over whether Briggs is trustworthy. Jakes and Briggs try to work out how he can get the tape during the mission the next day. He asks Jakes to bust Mike first when the tack team moves in so he can get the recording.

The next day Mike and Briggs and wait on the corner and Paige and Jakes wait with the tack team. Clayton shows up in a fancy car, the wrong one. They go with him after they confirm that he has the Crown Vic.

Charlie goes to Cortez for help to work on Quinn. She claims it should be an easy in and out. Johnny shows up and busts Cortez's balls. Cortez says he's not corrupt and he's on Charlie's side. Johnny says he's in. Jangles is not happy.

Clayton and the gang head to Koreatown to do the smash-and-grab. They put on ski masks, grab guns, and plan to knock off a "massage" parlor. Jakes and Paige and the tack team follow and wait for it to play out. Jakes and Paige bicker a bit knowing that they are on opposing "sides." Although Jakes claims he isn't on a specific side.

The gang, including Mike and Briggs, rampage through the parlor and busts the johns and grab their wallets. As they are about to jam, Mike handcuffs Briggs to a structure in the massage parlor. Briggs pulls his gun on him and threatens to shoot him. Mike begs him to let him prove him innocent and jumps into the getaway car.

Jakes comes in and uncuffs Briggs and asks him what he wants to do next since Mike knows where the car is and Briggs doesn't. Briggs says Mike beat him with a suckerpunch and that the game is over and he needs to go get a head start. Jakes asks a head start on what. Briggs says the rest of his life.

Charlie and Cortez go to see Quinn. Cortez is nervous. They try to convince Quinn to get him to text Odin and dangle Jangles. Quinn and Cortez get into it and Charlie says she'll take it from there. Quinn hits on her and she hits him.. They fight. She throws him into a table and starts beating his face in, remembering Whistler, her informant.

Clayton and the smash and grab gang arrive at the Crown Vic. Mike pulls his gun and announces he's a federal agent.

Briggs heads home to Graceland. It's empty.

The tack team arrives with Paige to the Crown Vic. Jakes is not with them.

Briggs moves aside an altar in Gracelnad and punches a hole in the wall. He pulls out a bag with money and passports.

Paige and Mike open the Crown Vic but the recorder is gone.

Briggs gives Graceland one last look and walks out.

description: In this season finale, the infamous Caza enforcer Jangles takes a member of Graceland hostage and the house must come together in order to save one of their own from a sadistic killer.
tags: ['serial killer', 'contraband', 'false identity', 'drinking', 'knife', 'fight', 'adolescent']
synopsis_with_character_names:
"Graceland" - "Pawn" - Sept. 12, 203

We pick up where we left off with Briggs bugging out of Graceland with a bag full of cash, passports and ID. He gets a call from Mike as he's leaving but he ignores him.

Mike sends out an APB on Briggs and Johnny gets it as he's going into Graceland. Briggs bluffs that it's part of his cover with the Caza cartel and Johnny lets him leave.

Briggs has Jakes drop him off at the marina saying he's hopping a boat to his new life and they say their goodbyes.

But you know our boy Briggs is more crafty than that.

He meets up with the drug dealer Quinn who worked for Odin but didn't know him. Since Charlie put the fear of Jangles into him, Quinn wants to skip town. Briggs gives him the new IDs and passports with the name Tony Brusca. Quinn hands him cash and hops a boat to Ecuador.

Jakes calls Briggs and tells him that Charlie has been working with a Federale. He puts it together with what he saw on the surveillance video at the Diane hotel. Briggs drives to where he buried Juan Badillo and grabs the key labeled Apt. 3 off the body. He then goes looking for Jangles. Jakes also tells Briggs there's no recording.

Everyone in the house is interrogated and the house is swept and the roommates begin fighting with many considering Mike a rat and there is fear that Graceland will be shut down. Johnny asks Jakes why Briggs didn't come to him for help and Jakes says he needs to grow up. Mike wants to find Briggs and keep Graceland open.

Mike works on figuring out what Briggs is doing. He works out that he's still in L.A. and gets excited. In his excitement he kisses Paige. She stops him and says she would be willing but not like this because it's not about her.

Briggs shows up at Jakes' son's soccer game. Briggs tells him about Charlie and Jangles but Jakes doesn't want to hear it since what he's done has sent the house into a frenzy of trouble.

Charlie meets with Jangles and has a drink. They toast to mending a broken heart. She begs off going home with him. But then has a change of heart and heads to the house where he is staying on the beach.

Briggs has arrived first, however. He enters and manages to put the Badillo key on Jangles' keychain but he hears him and comes down and confronts him. They fight. Charlie enters confused and Jangles knocks Briggs out and tells Charlie to cuff him. But, of course, he then turns on her and assaults her and holds both her and Briggs hostage.

He forces Briggs to watch as he hurts Charlie, cutting her with a knife. Thanks to GPS tracking, Mike arrives to save the day. He enters the house and Jangles confronts him and Mike shoots him. He rescues Briggs ad Charlie and Charlie kicks Jangles' body on the way out.

Briggs asks Mike how he figured it out. Mike explains and then Birggs also explains more fully. It turns out that while he was shooting up Briggs all he wanted to know was who the mole in the Caza cartel was. After getting him hooked, they left him to detox and he became so crazed that he gave up a fellow agent as the mole. That agent also lived in the Estate and Jangles went and burned the house down, killing Lisa, Briggs' girlfriend, as well.

Mike learns he's getting shipped to D.C. to become the special assistant to the deputy director.

The Feds find the evidence that Jangles killed Badillo-- the key that Briggs put on him. They also believe that Quinn, now on the run in Ecuador, is the infamous Odin Rossi. Briggs got off and is free as a bird. Charlie apologizes to Briggs and says she is wracked with guilt, saying she's going to turn in her badge. Briggs says the house needs her. They hug.

Briggs tells Jakes they're even. They both wonder where the recording is. Neither knows. Jakes tells Briggs he now needs to fix Graceland. (Especially since he knows that Briggs killed Juan.)

The housemates have a bonfire. Briggs makes a speech about heroin addiction and says he forgot about home and apologizes. They toast Mike's return back to East Coast. Briggs and Mike smile at each other.

Back in D.C. going over stuff in a high level meeting, Mike reminisces about Graceland.

We cut to a pawn shop. Two teen boys approach a tape recorder. They press play and we hear Briggs' murder of Juan Badillo. They take the tape.

Briggs calls Mike just to check in. The season ends with Briggs saying to Mike, "Listen I haven't told anyone else about this..."

description: When Steve Rogers is seriously injured, Peggy Carter becomes the world's first super soldier.
tags: ['world war two', 'super soldier', 'shield', 'mechanical armor', 'peggy carter character', 'steve rogers character', 'howard stark character', 'bucky barnes character', 'red skull character', 'arnim zola character', 'dum dum dugan character', 'hydra', 'train', 'castle', 'tesseract', 'portal to another dimension', 'interdimensional portal', 'interdimensional monster', 'tentacle', 'tentacled creature', 'alternate history', 'alternate universe', 'alternate timeline', 'female soldier', 'misogyny', 'sexism', 'feminism', 'reference to hedy lamarr', 'reference to brooklyn new york city', 'exo suit', 'mech suit', 'robot suit', 'scientist', 'playboy', 'general', 'war hero', 'soldier', 'nazi', 'monster', 'tentacle monster', 'serum', 'superhuman strength', 'superhuman', 'germany', 'norway', 'explosion', 'saboteur', 'vibranium', 'nick fury character', 'clint barton character']
synopsis_with_character_names:
The alien Watcher talks about the limitless possibilities that make up the multiverse, and where a single different choice can create a different reality.

-----

On Earth in 1943, the Nazis spread out from Germany and across Europe. The Allied scientists band together to create a super-soldier, and Steve Rogers becomes Captain America. But in a different universe, a different choice created a new hero.

Peggy Carter and Steve watch the preparations for the super-soldier program, and Peggy points out that if the project works, Steve could end the war. They approach the head scientist, Abraham Erskine, and Peggy says that she prefers to stay rather than watch from the booth. She and the observers step back as Steve is put in the machine. Peggy sees one of the "observers" use a remote to trigger a planted explosive before she can stop him, and the saboteur runs to the transformation chamber. He shoots Steve when the latter tries to stop him, then grabs a vial of the serum as Howard Stark looks on.

Stepping up, Peggy shoots the saboteur dead. She runs to Steve and Howard says that they're losing the power levels and need to activate the process now. When the commander, Colonel John Flynn, orders Howard to get into the chamber, Howard says that he's not a soldier but it has to be now. Peggy puts the vial back in the machine, gets in, and Howard activates the process. When the process is over, the chamber opens and Peggy emerges, larger and more muscular.

As the doctors take blood samples from Peggy, Flynn complains that they've wasted money. He tells Peggy that all of Erskine's serum went into her, and analysis of her blood might show them how to make a "real" super-soldier. He dismisses women as not soldiers, much to Peggy's disgust, and walks off.

Later, Peggy works out in the gym working a bag. Steve watches as Peggy knocks the bag across the room, and throws another weight into the wall in anger. The 107th march past outside, and Steve says that his friend Bucky is with them and they are deploying but the Army won't tell Steve where Bucky is going. Steve tells Peggy that she'll be the one to end the war, and the two of them flirt briefly.

Nazi forces led by Hydra take over the town of Tensberg, Norway, and Howard detects gamma radiation from the clock tower. The power levels could power London for a century, or destroy it.

Johann Schmidt leads the Nazis in Tensberg, and finds the Tesseract hidden in the church. The soldiers kill the priest guarding it.

Howard and Peggy have done research on the Tesseract, and Howard wants to send a team to take it on its way to Berlin. Flynn objects, and refuses to let Peggy go when she volunteers. The colonel figures the war will be over before Hydra figures out how to use the Tesseract.

Peggy goes to a bar and drinks, and Howard joins her and gives a costume and a shield.

Soldiers accompany Arnim Zola and the Tesseract into Berlin via motorcade. Peggy attacks the motorcade using her shield. She then jumps down from a building and uses her shield and her super-strength to flip the lead truck. Peggy takes down the remaining soldiers and then takes out a burly soldier in hand-to-hand after he challenges her.

Peggy steps into the back of the truck where Zola is still sitting, takes the Tesseract and returns to the Allied base and shows it to Flynn. She tells him that they won't win the war with her stuck behind a desk, and Flynn tells her that she's not qualified for field duty. Peggy tells Flynn to promote her to captain and leaves. Howard is there, and says that he knows what to do with the Tesseract.

Later, Howard makes a large metal suit as Steve looks on. Howard asks Steve if he's ready to join the war effort.

Later, Peggy and Steve confirm where the 107th are pinned down by enemy fire. As they prepare to leave, Steve takes Peggy's hand and says that he owes Peggy one. Peggy tells him that Steve owes her a dance and squeezes his hand.

In the field, Peggy takes a soldier's motorcycle and crashes through the gate leading to a factory. She takes out the soldiers on guard, finds the prisoners including Dum Dum Dugan. Bucky is there, and asks who Peggy is supposed to be, and Peggy rips his cell door off with her bare hands. Peggy says that Steve sent her, and she's Captain Carter.

Peggy and the 107th fight their way out, and Nazi tanks arrive. They take cover and Peggy calls in air support, and Steve flies in wearing the battlesuit Howard made for him. Using the suit's enhanced strength, Steve stops one tank and then several more with the suit's weaponry. Peggy joins him and together they take out the remaining tanks. As the 107th join them, Steve opens up his suit and leads a cheer for Captain Carter.

Soon Peggy is fighting more Nazis. Flynn is taking credit for "his" decision", and tells the President that he told Howard to build the "Hydra Stomper". The two of them fly up and take out Nazi fighters.

At Castle Krake in Germany, Johann is examining the plaque that concealed the Tesseract. Hitler demands that Johann come to Berlin, and Johann says that a "god" doesn't answer to a man. Johann tells the officer sent to escort him that soon the true champion of Hydra will be summoned from beyond the stars. When the office questions him, Johann shoots him dead and his men hold the officer's guards at gunpoint. Johann pulls off his human mask, revealing a skinless red skull beneath and says that Hydra will rise from the Third Reich's ashes.

Peggy and Steve share a drink, and Steve tells Peggy that she's always been a fighter. He admits that he envies the respect Peggy receives, and Peggy assures him that he's her hero. Steve tells Peggy that she's his hero. Bucky and Howard arrive and Howard realizes that something is going on between Peggy and Steve.

Peggy, Bucky, and a squad of soldiers intercept the train Red Skull is on, but Bucky figures that it's a trap. Steve flies up in the Hydra Stomper and stops the train, and the others drop down on lines onto the top of the train. Steve breaks into the train and finds explosives but no sign of Red Skull. As Steve yells a warning to the others, the explosives go off. Peggy and the others leap off the back of the train, and the mountain collapses into the crevasse alongside the tracks.

Running to the wreckage, Peggy looks for Steve. The mountain starts to come down, and Bucky tells Peggy that they have to go. They leave just as an avalanche comes down.

Later, Peggy, Howard, and Flynn meet in Flynn's office and Flynn complains that they failed. Peggy reminds Flynn that they lost Steve, not just a battlesuit, and walks off. She goes to the imprisoned Zola, who says that he will tell her nothing.

After a few minutes of interrogation, Peggy tells the others that Zola told her everything. Red Skull believes he can unleash an interdimensional force that will lead Hydra to world domination, or world annihilation. Red Skull is at Krake, and Peggy says that it's time to take the fight to Red Skull. She warns that they might not succeed in ending the war or themselves survive, but they will stop Hydra. The others agree to take the mission--for Steve-- and even Howard agrees to go with them.

Soon, Peggy infiltrates Krake and opens the gate so the others can enter. They split up, Peggy and Howard going one way while the soldiers go another.

Red Skull puts the Tesseract in a machine of his own devising and has one of his men activate the machine. The Tesseract opens a portal. Bucky and the soldiers shoot their way into a room, and find Hydra Stomper fastened powerless into a holding device.

Peggy and Howard find the chamber with the Tesseract.

A gigantic tentacle creature emerges from the portal, and Red Skull laughs in triumph and declares that the champion of Hydra has risen. Peggy bursts in and Johann tells her that she's too late. The creature grabs and crushes Red Skull.

Bucky finds Steve nearby, manacled, and Steve tells Bucky to get him into the suit. They do so and hook the suit up to power it temporarily, Hydra Stomper falls over, and then then Steve flies through the ceiling to the Tesseract room.

The creature continues growing and wreaking havoc, and Peggy gets Howard to the controls to reverse the polarity of the portal and send the creature back. A tentacle pins Peggy to a wall, and she grabs a nearby sword and cuts herself free. As more tentacles pin Peggy down, Howard reverses the polarity and the creature is pulled back through the portal. Peggy anchors herself with the sword, and Steve blasts through the floor.

A tentacle slams him into a wall, and Peggy cuts him free. The soldiers arrive and open fire, and Steve joins them. The creature howls and deafens everyone, and Steve gets them out to safety then flies back in.

The creature holds the portal open so Howard can't close it, and Peggy shoves it back using her shield. Steve flies in and blasts the tentacles, but his suit runs out of power and crashes. Steve crawls out of the suit and tells Peggy to stop, and she tells him that she has to. Peggy tells Steve that they'll dance the next Saturday night, then pushes the creature back through the portal and herself along with it. The portal closes and explodes, leaving the Tesseract on the floor. Steve kneels next to it, realizing that it's taken Peggy from him.

Now

A new portal opens due to the Tesseract and Peggy emerges from it. Nick Fury and Clint Barton are there, and Nick tells Peggy that the war has been over for over 70 years Peggy says that they'll be okay, because they won the war.

description: The rough-and-tumble space pirates known as the Ravagers abduct T'Challa instead of Peter Quill.
tags: ['pirate', "t'challa character", 'wakanda', 'outer space', 'reference to black panther', 'alternate history', 'alternate timeline', 'alternate universe', 'star lord character', 'alternate reality', 'alien planet', 'alien world', 'outlaw', 'orb', 'electrocution', 'ravager', 'spaceship', 'space travel', 'yondu character', 'alien', 'humanoid alien', 'year 1988', 'flashback', 'kingdom', 'king', 'prince', 'spear', 'abducted by aliens', 'mix up', 'vibranium', 'reference to peter quill', 'new recruit', 'heist', 'theft', 'thanos character', 'bar', 'drax the destroyer character', 'bartender', 'nebula character', 'peekaboo hairdo', 'father daughter relationship', 'adoptive father adopted daughter relationship', 'collector', 'kingpin', 'reference to robin hood', 'band of outlaws', 'knowhere', 'distraction', 'diversion', 'betrayal']
synopsis_with_character_names:
On the abandoned planet Morag, a masked Star Lord enters an ancient temple. He uses a device to pull a force-field encased sphere to him. Korath and two of his men enter, aim their guns at Star Lord, and tell him to drop the sphere. Star Lord removes his mask revealing that he's Prince T'Challa of Earth, and Korath says that he's a huge fan of Star Lord.

Korath tells has men to stand down, saying that it's the Star Lord, the legendary outlaw who steals from the rich and gives to the poor, and admits that he would like to join the Ravagers. The alien regrets that he has to take the sphere from T'Challa, and offers to fight him without his gun. T'Challa tells him to use it, and fights Korath barehanded. He suckers Korath into hitting the charged force field, and Korath is stunned unconscious. The two men open fire on T'Challa, who dodges their blasts, takes cover, and uses his device to stun them.

T'Challa runs outside with Korath, and finds more soldiers waiting. He tells them that as a Ravager, he's never alone. Yondu uses his Yakka arrow to kill the soldiers, and T'Challa shows him the sphere. The Ravager jokingly says that they could sell, it, and T'Challa figures it'd be put to better use jumpstarting a race's star. Their ship lands nearby, and they board and depart.

Earth, Wakanda: 1988

A young T'Challa tells his father, Baba, that he wants to go out to see the world. Baba warns him that the world is full of war and hatred, and has nothing to offer Wakanda. He understands that T'Challa has the heart of an explorer, but warns that all T'Challa will find if he goes there will be pain and destruction.

Later, T'Challa throws his spear outside of the nation's force field and goes out to retrieve it. A Ravager ship arrives on Earth to abduct the child of Ego, and Yondu sends Kraglin and Taserface to get the child. They take T'Challa by mistake and bring him to Yondu, who realizes their error. The two Ravagers explain that they detected cosmic energy, and T'Challa explains that his home is built on Vibranium. When T'Challa says that he was out exploring, Yondu invites him to explore a galaxy's worth of worlds.

20 Years Later

T'Challa and the other Ravagers go to a planet and drink, initiating their new member Korath. Thanos, a Ravager, joins them, and explains that T'Challa showed him there's more than one way to reallocate the galaxy's resources. T'Challa goes to the bar and buys a drink from the bartender, Drax. When Drax realizes that T'Challa saved his homeworld, along with Drax's wife and children, he's happy to meet T'Challa. Nebula, all gussied up, joins them and says that T'Challa looks pretty good to her.

T'Challa and Nebula grab a table to have a drink, and T'Challa suggests that she talk to her father, Thanos. Nebula refuses, figure that he hasn't changed, and asks if he's ever considered going back to Wakanda. T'Challa explains that Yondu tried to take him back when T'Challa was young, but Wakanda had been destroyed in a senseless war like Baba warned T'Challa about. Nebula figures that T'Challa saves homes because he lost his own, and tells him that she has a job for him.

Later, Nebula briefs the Ravagers on the Embers of Genesis, that can terraform entire ecosystems. With the Embers they could eradicate hunger across the galaxy. The Collector has the Embers, and he's the most ruthless kingpin in the intergalactic underworld. He took over when Thanos went straight. Yondu warns T'Challa that the mission is suicide, and says that the Ravagers aren't going.

T'Challa talks to Yondu privately and says that Ravagers don't back down from a fight. Yondu reluctantly gives in, and they go to the mining colony of Knowhere where the Collector has his base. The Black Order is working security for Collector, and Nebula and Yondu go in posing as sellers of the sphere. T'Challa is inside the case they're carrying, and Proxima Midnight is running security. She scans the case, while Korath and Thanos start a fight outside. The Black Guards check it out, including Midnight, while T'Challa emerges from the case and goes to search for the Embers. At least, that's the plan.

Nebula and Yondu get into to see Collector. Meanwhile, T'Challa searches the collection, which is bigger than he anticipated. He finds Howard the Duck and asks the captive if he knows where the Embers are. Howard can barely describe where they are verbally, and T'Challa shoots the lock off of his container and takes Howard with him.

The Ravagers fight their staged fight until Midnight, use an energy blast from her staff to paralyze them. She recognizes them and realizes that it's a diversion, and sounds the alarms.

Howard stops to get a drink, and the alarms go off and the doors seal off. T'Challa gets out just in time, and his necklace from Earth glows. A nearby Wakanda shuttle on display activates, and T'Challa boards it. There are dummies of Wakandan pilots onboard, and a hologram of Baba activates when T'Challa speaks.

Bama talks about how his son T'Challa was abducted, and asks for anyone with information about the boy's whereabouts should respond to the homing beacon. Baba then says that in case T'Challa is listening, that they will search every world until they find T'Challa.

Nebula comes in and holds a gun on T'Challa. Collector is with her, holding Yondu prisoner, and Nebula says that she owed Collector a debt and T'Challa was the payment.

T'Challa is tossed in a cell with the other prisoners, and Korath figures that T'Challa plans an escape Instead, T'Challa grabs Yondu and says that he lied to him about Wakanda's destruction. Yondu insists that he was protecting T'Challa, and T'Challa is just like him. T'Challa says that he's nothing like Yondu, and Yondu tells him that he's an explorer and the past is nothing but a prison. When Yondu says that the Ravagers are T'Challa's family, T'Challa tells him that the Ravagers aren't his family and never were.

Ebony Maw comes and takes T'Challa to Collector. Collector puts T'Challa in a containment cell and plans to use him to decorate a wall. Unimpressed, Collector tells his minions to dissect T'Challa.

Nebula goes to the Ravagers' cell, and she shoots Ebony Maw dead and says that she's there to rescue them. She explains that the entire thing was her plan, and she told T'Challa about it from the beginning. It was T'Challa's idea to keep them in the dark, because he knew Yondu would never let T'Challa walk into a trap, and T'Challa being captured gave her the opportunity to steal the Embers.

T'Challa uses his necklace to break out of the cell, and Carina turns against her superior and shoots him from behind. As T'Challa runs through the containment cells, Collector uses the weapons in the collection against T'Challa.

The Ravagers run with the Black Order following them, and Thanos tells the others to go on while he attacks their pursuers alone. Thanos fights the Black Order brawler, Black Dwarf, When Midnight joins the fight and wounds Thanos, Nebula turns to watch.

Collector tells T'Challa that his new family has abandoned him. Yondu returns and uses his arrow to knock off the helm that Collector is using. Collector grabs and snaps the arrow when Yondu sends it at him.

Midnight and Dwarf beat Thanos down, and Midnight prepares to kill him. Nebula arrives and shoots Midnight, and Dwarf grabs Nebula and she feeds him the Embers. They grow within him, and Thanos and Nebula run and jump aboard the Ravager ship just as it lifts off. Nebula figures that Yondu and T'Challa are doing fine.

Collector beats Yondu, until T'Challa joins the fight. Yondu gets close enough to Collector to steal his control bracelet, and T'Challa uses it to open a cell and knocks Collector inside, before sealing it shut. Collector vows to hunt them down, and they give the bracelet to Carina who uses it to free Collector's "collection". They're not happy with Collector.

T'Challa and Yondu fly out of Knowhere using the Wakandan shuttle, they head to the rendezvous to meet the others, and Yondu starts to apologize. His adopted son tells him that there's no need, because Yondu showed him the universe just like he wanted. T'Challa admits that he doesn't know where he belongs, and Yondu assures T'Challa that there's no place where he doesn't belong. He asks where T'Challa wants to be and brings up a hologram of Earth, and tells T'Challa to follow his heart.

The Ravagers go to Earth and Wakanda, and they go the throne room to meet Baba. T'Challa introduces his "family", and they have a celebration. Baba asks Yondu how T'Challa ended up with him, and T'Challa jumps in to say that he was lost and Yondu found him.

Peter Quill is working as a janitor at a Dairy Queen. As he cleans up after hours, Ego comes in and asks Peter if he can spare some time for his father.

description: Nick Fury struggles to launch The Avengers when candidates are targeted by a serial killer.

synopsis_with_character_names:
Monday

Nick Fury is driving with Natasha Romanoff, aka Black Widow, talking about the idea of the Avengers Initiative. She's surprised that Nick wants to bet the future of the Initiative on Tony Stark, who is sitting and eating donuts. Nick thinks that Tony has potential.

Nick calls Tony into the donut shop and they sit at a table. He says that Tony has become a problem that he has to deal with, and points out the poisonous veins on Tony's neck. Natasha injects Tony in the neck with lithium dioxide, and Nick explains that it will take the edge off of the poisoning. Tony gags and collapses, and Natasha confirms that Tony is dead.

-----

The Watcher talks about how Iron Man, Hulk, and Thor were encountered in one week and became members of the Avengers.

-----

Tuesday

Thor's hammer Mjolnir rests in a crater. Agent Phil Coulson of SHIELD calls Nick and reports that they found it, and the locals are getting curious. Nick is busy with something else, and tells Coulson to have his team set up a perimeter. Natasha is brought out of prison and insists that she didn't kill Tony. The SHIELD guards have Nick escort her to the transport truck and he who says that he believes that she's innocent but his hands are tied.

Nick slips Natasha an injector, and says that someone in SHIELD poisoned Tony so he needs her to escape and find out who. Nick escorts her to the transport and she gets in, and Nick watches the truck drive off. Inside Natasha escapes her handcuffs and knocks out her guards. The two men upfront hear the noise and stop the truck, and when they open the back doors they discover the guards unconscious and Natasha gone.

In Puente Antiguo, New Mexico, where the crater is, Nick and Clint Barton watch SHIELD scientists scan Mjolnir. Nick figures someone will come looking for it, and Coulson finds one of several guards down and sounds the alarms. Going to the command center, Nick tells Coulson to give him an update. Coulson spots the intruder that knocked out the guards and is knocking out more, and is impressed by Thor's "great hair".

Barton goes up on a crane-lifted platform and draws an arrow. Thor goes to Mjolnir and reaches for it, and Nick tells Barton to hold his fire. Barton shoots Thor in the chest, killing him. Barton says that he didn't shoot, and SHIELD security officers train their guns on him anyway. Nick arrives and points out that it's Barton's arrow in Thor's chest.

Later, Barton sits in a cell insisting he never slips and never misfires. Nick and Coulson watch him, and Nick has confirmed that Thor is almost a thousand years old. Going in, Nick approaches Barton and discovers that he's dead. Later Nick tells Coulson that Barton wouldn't have killed himself because he has a wife and kids, and figures whoever killed Stark killed Thor and Barton. Coulson points out that Barton was alone in a cell under observation, and there were no signs of a struggle. Nick admits that he has one idea of what connects them.

Wednesday

At Culver University in Virginia, Natasha approaches Betty Ross and she says that she hasn't seen "him". Natasha says that she's there about Tony, and believes that he was murdered. She shows Ross the injector Nick slipped her earlier, and explains that she needed someone to check it out outside of SHIELD.

Ross and Natasha go to Ross' lab, and Ross examines the injector. There's no trace of lethal pathogens, and the antidote didn't make it out of the syringe. A tiny projectile of some sort was fired from the needle, and Ross says that they're done. As Natasha leaves, she notices a pizza joint baseball cap. Ross claims that a student left it there. Nick calls Natasha and tells her that Barton is dead. Natasha asks who she kills, and Nick figures that the killer is going after the Initiative candidates. Bruce Banner and Natasha are the last two living candidates, and Nick tells her to hide after finding Banner.

Natasha notices Ross glancing at a door, and goes to it. Ross stops Natasha from opening the door, and Banner comes out and says that there's no need for violence. Natasha hears cars outside and says that they need to go.

At the SHIELD desert base, a beam of energy shoots down from the sky. An army of Asgardian soldiers materialize, Loki leading them. SHIELD assault soldiers arrive, and Nick steps out. Loki tells him to kneel before a god, and Nick's phone rings interrupting Loki's introductory speech.

Natasha leads Banner off and calls Nick, and soldiers surround them. General Ross tells his men to move on his mark.

Nick finally answers his phone, and Natasha tells him what's going on. He tells Natasha to deal with it and hangs up, and Loki says that vengeance brought him there.

Natasha introduces herself to the soldiers, says that she has Banner in her custody, and tells them to stand down. Someone sniper shoots Banner in the shoulder, but all of Ross' soldiers report that they didn't shoot.

Loki brings out an energy-charged box.

Banner tells Natasha to run as his eyes turn green.

When Nick asks what's in the box, Loki says that he will take Earth as retribution for Nick's insolence.

Banner turns into Hulk and Natasha runs. Ross has his men open fire.

Loki releases a blast of energy from the box, freezing the SHIELD assault officers.

Hulk smashes the soldier's vehicles. He throws a jeep at Natasha, who dodges, then grabs Ross as she runs to her father. Meanwhile, Hulk swells up and explodes.

Nick tells Loki that what he's doing won't bring Thor back. Lady Sif tells Loki to stop, agreeing with Nick, and Nick tells Loki that they have the same enemy: the person who killed Thor also killed Tony and Barton. He assures Loki that when he finds Thor's killer, Loki will have his vengeance. Loki gives him until the next sunrise to deliver his brother's assassin.

At a public library in Manassas, Virginia, Natasha accesses a computer and calls Coulson to get his SHIELD password because she's locked out of the system. He finally gives it to her, and Natasha hears someone moving behind her. She looks, but there's no one there. Natasha brings up a file on Hope Van Dyne, and confirms that she accessed the database the day before.

Natasha calls Nick, but then hears the person behind her again. She turns to face him, and tells him he won't win against SHIELD or her. Her attacker easily throws Natasha around, and she tries to reach her dropped phone to leave message on Nick's voicemail, but is pulled away by her attacker, yelling that it's all about Hope.

Later at a diner in the nearby town, Nick listens to Natasha's message. Coulson tells Nick that there's four hours until sunrise, and says that Nick is the only Initiative candidate still alive. Nick says that he's not the only Avenger left, goes out to his car, takes a signal device out of the glove compartment, and tells Coulson that it's their last hope. He has an idea about Hope, then puts the device back in the glove compartment and goes to meet with Loki.

Nick drives to the ice palace Loki has set up, and confronts the Destroyer on guard.

Thursday

In a graveyard in San Francisco, Nick goes to the tombstone of Hope Van Dyne, and hears someone behind him. Nick calls to Hank Pym, who steps out of the fog in his Yellow Jacket armor. Hank says Nick has no right to come there and stand over Hope's grave, and Hank says that Hope is dead because SHIELD killed her, and died because of Nick.

Nick says that Hope was killed on a mission, and Hank points out that Hope was his daughter and Nick exploited her grief for her mother. Because Hope died like her mother died, Hank murdered the others so he could destroy everything Nick worked for. He killed Thor figuring Nick would recruit him, convincing Thor that he was a hero.

Yellow Jacket shrinks and attacks Nick, and Nick holds his own. He flips over Yellow Jacket, much to the killer's surprise, then punches Yellow Jacket across the graveyard. When Yellow Jacket comes at him, Nick slaps him down and disappears, then reappears and taunts Yellow Jacket.

Yellow Jacket blasts Nick, who disappears and reappears behind the killer. He teleports away from Yellow Jacket's attacks, then an army of Nick's appear. Yellow Jacket flies up, but a giant Nick appears behind him and an icicle grows up from below, encasing Yellow Jacket. Yellow Jacket falls to the ground, and the Nicks laugh at him. They turn into Loki, who drops his multiple illusions.

Nick joins Loki, and Nick tells Hank that SHIELD is people willing to give their lives for something greater than themselves, to save the world from men like Hank. After Nick removes the power pack from the suit, Loki's soldiers capture Hank. As the soldiers take Hank away, Hank tells Nick to honor Hope. Loki tells Nick that it was a pleasure, and Nick tells him to get off the planet. The Asgardian says that he might stay on Earth for a while.

Friday

At the UN Building, Loki and his soldiers enter the building and Loki says that the nations of Earth have set aside their differences and united under his command. His words are broadcast across the planet as Loki says that humans crave domination and were made to be ruled.

At a hangar, Nick and Coulson look at the coffins of the six victims. Nick says that the would-be Avengers may rest in peace, but they won't. He tells Coulson that the Avengers were meant to be an affirmation of humanity's strength, and goes to a piece of an iceberg containing Captain America. Captive Marvel arrives and asks where the fight is.

synopsis_with_character_names:
Dr. Stephen Strange picks up his girlfriend Christine Palmer and they ride along a stretch of highway. As they drive, Christine asks Stephen to say the speech he's giving later at an award ceremony for the procedure he performed in surgery. She tells Stephen to rush the podium, screaming and cheering, Stephen swerves around a truck and brakes to avoid an oncoming car. He manages to brake, but another car slams into them from behind and knocks them off the highway.

When the car lands, Stephen lives but realizes that Christine is dead. He travels the world searching the mystic arts for a way to bring Christine back, and gains the Eye of Agamotto which supposedly can alter timelines. Wong and the Ancient One warn Stephen that tampering with time can destroy the universe, and they protect reality rather than threaten it.

The Ancient One still died and Stephen bargains with Dormammu, but Stephen can't let go of the past. Two years after Christine's death, Stephen is in his Sanctum with Wong. Wong notices that Stephen has the Eye, but says nothing and goes to the kitchen and advises Stephen not to do something reckless. Once he's alone, Stephen puts on the Eye and uses it to travel back through time to the point where he picked up Christine on the night she died.

The accident happens as before despite Stephen's efforts, and Christine still dies. He uses the Eye to rewind time and takes a different route, but another car slams into them and Christine dies. No matter what Stephen does, Christine dies of one cause or another

Watcher: In this universe, Stephen Strange didn't lose his hands, but his heart. Even Stephen avoids picking up Christine, she dies in a fire. He goes back and meets Christine, and wonders if they're allowed to be happy. Christine drives and they're knocked off the road by another car again, and Christine dies.

Stephen crawls from the wreckage, and screams in anguish. The Ancient One appears and says that she's there to help him. She says that Stephen ill seek answers in the mystic arts and in her, and says that Christine's death is an absolute and unchangeable point in time. Without Christine's death, Stephen would never have become the Sorcerer Supreme. The Ancient One says that Stephen is risking the universe, and Stephen figures that all he needs is more power. She tells Stephen to stop torturing himself, and he can't save Christine. The Ancient One says that the path he's on only leads to darkness and the end of reality.

When Stephen refuses to stop, the Ancient One unleashes a blast of energy. Later Stephen enters a jungle looking for the lost library of Cagliostro. He comes across a man, O'Bengh, who walks away without a word. Stephen follows him to a nearby temple, and Stephen teleports in. Glowing sigils appear and drop Stephen into a cave. O'Bengh comes up, and says that he's the librarian for Cagliostro's books.

O'Bengh takes Stephen to a chamber with the books, and says that a sorcerer can gain the necessary power by absorbing the energy of other beings. Stephen summons a massive tentacle creature and asks if it can share some of its power with him. The creature attacks Stephen, and O'Bengh tends to Stephen afterward. He asks if Christine is worth the pain, and warns that love can break a person's mind. With that, O'Bengh leaves.

Stephen soon realizes that he has to take the power he wants. He takes a Cloak of Levitation from one creature he summons, and absorbs dozens of others.

The Watcher secretly watches, realizing Stephen is on the wrong path. However, the Watcher won't risk the safety of all the other universes. The being also figures that Stephen wouldn't listen.

Once Stephen has enough power, he summons the tentacled creature and absorbs it as well.

Stephen goes to O'Bengh, who is now old and dying. He refuses to let Stephen restore his youth. When Stephen says that he can't accept that, O'Bengh hopes that the other Stephen will. O'Bengh tells Stephen that he is only half a man.

Centuries ago, on the second anniversary of Christine's death, Stephen sets aside the Eye and decides to stop living in the past. He goes out and sees the world dissolving, the people along with it. The Ancient One appears, says that she's an "echo", and warns that they don't have much time. She tells Stephen that he's causing the destruction, when another version of him used the Eye and vanished into the past where she couldn't follow.

When the Ancient One attacked Stephen earlier, she caused two his possible timelines to exist in one universe. She warns that if the other Stephen succeeds in reversing an absolute point in their universe, the paradox will destroy their universe. The Ancient One says that the only sorcerer strong enough to stop the other Stephen is Stephen.

Stephen returns to the Sanctum and tells Wong what is happening. Wong asks if Stephen wants to stop his counterpart, and Stephen says that he has to. When Wong casts a protection spell on him, Stephen accepts it and is teleported away by the other Stephen.

Stephen is imprisoned in a magic circle, and the dark Stephen steps out of the shadows and says that they are one and the same. He says that they knew and loved Christine, and Stephen tells his counterpart that he can't bring Christine back. Dark Stephen says that he sacrificed everything for Christine, and they have to save her together.

Dark Stephen teleports Stephen to the car wreck, and says that their powers are divided but once they become whole again, they can save Christine. Stephen says that they can't and repeats the Ancient One's, and Dark Stephen insists that the Ancient One doesn't understand. Despite that, Stephen says it's arrogance, not love.

The spell protects Stephen from Dark Stephen's initial attack. The two sorcerers fight, as do their Cloaks. Stephen casts his most powerful spell, but Dark Stephen survives and pulls his counterpart into the shadows. Christine appears and says that they can be together again, but Stephen remembers the world dissolving and pulls away. Dark Stephen drops the illusion and attacks Stephen. He ends the protection spell and takes Stephen's power, and uses the power to bring Christine back.

Christine recoils in terror at the sight of Dark Stephen, transformed into a demonic being by the power he's absorbed. She starts to dissolve, and he uses all of his magic to hold back the dissolution. The Watcher appears outside the protective bubble, and Stephen asks him to stop the dissolution. Stephen admits that he was wrong, and the world shouldn't suffer for his arrogance. The Watcher says that he would punish Stephen if he could, but he can't interfere because it will cause more destruction.

The Watcher departs and the universe ends. Stephen creates a protective shell, but Christine dissolves in his hands. He collapses in grief, saying that he's sorry.

synopsis_with_character_names: When Bruce Banner is teleported by Heimdall to Earth to pass the warning about Thanos to the Avengers, he finds New York empty until Thanos' minions arrive. They are beaten down by shadowed figures who turn out to be murderous zombie versions of Iron Man, Wong and Stephen Strange. He is rescued from their attack by the Wasp and Spider-Man, assisted by Dr Strange's sentient Cloak of Levitation. The Watcher reveals that Janet Van Dyne in the Quantum Realm was the source of the zombie infection and passed it to Hank Pym and Scott Lang when Pym tried to rescue her. Within 24 hours the West Coast of USA was infected and within two weeks it had spread from the Avengers to the whole planet. Peter Parker shows his orientation video about rules for surviving a zombie apocalypse. The other survivors include Happy Hogan, Kurt from Scott Lang's crew, Bucky Barnes, Sharon Carter and Okoye. They track a garbled message about a cure to Camp Lehigh, and try to use the rail system to reach there. At Grand Central Station they are attacked by zombies including Hawkeye and Falcon. Happy Hogan gets infected. Spider-Man and Wasp find ways to jump start a train. Zombie Captain America boards the train and infects Sharon Carter, who infects Hope Van Dyne before the Cap and Carter zombies are destroyed. Peter Parker shares his thoughts on staying upbeat despite your losses. They reach the vicinity of Camp Lehigh. Hope Van Dyne sacrifices her giant-sized self to get the others across a mass of zombies. The survivors discover that the Vision or more specifically his Mind Stone is the potential cure, demonstrated by the restoration of humanity to the reanimated head of Scott Lang, currently occupying a glass jar. It is revealed that Vision was keeping a zombie Wanda Maximoff on the base and feeding her the survivors who responded to the message, including a leg-amputated but living T'Challa. Bucky encounters a hungry Wanda; Kurt and Okoye fall to her. Scott Lang gets his mobility back from being carried by the Cloak of Levitation. Vision realizes he has to help the survivors take the Mind Stone to Wakanda to then use it to save the world. He removes it from his brow ending his artificial life. Wanda throws Bucky through the sky. Bruce Banner finally gets Hulk to come out to and fight Wanda while the last three fly a Quadjet from the base. The jet is briefly delayed by the zombie giant Hope, then heads for Wakanda. Peter Parker grieves and Scott and T'Challa offers words of comfort. The final scene and hints from the Watcher reveal that Wakanda is now occupied by the zombie plague, and by a zombie Thanos carrying a nearly complete Infinity Gauntlet. He lacks only the Mind Stone which the heroes are currently bringing towards him.

synopsis_with_character_names: Arms manufacturer Tony Stark dodges an attack while visiting US military operations in Afghanistan. His savior is a black-ops SEAL named Erik Stevens AKA Killmonger. Back in the US, Killmonger declares he was in deep cover with the Ten Rings organization and exposes Stark Industries executive Obadiah Stane as the client who ordered the attack on Stark. Tony takes on Killmonger as the replacement executive, then invests in Killmonger's combat drone project. Pepper Potts asks Colonel Rhodes to dig into why Killmonger is trying to get influence with Tony. Killmonger points Tony to black-market vibranium as a power source for the drones. He manipulates Rhodes to approach Ulysses Klaue to buy vibranium, despite Pepper's objections. Killmonger uses the meeting with Klaue to draw out T'Challa and kill him, and pin it on the murdered Rhodes. Klaue reveals he is Killmonger's partner in all this and hands off the vibranium. Tony reveals that he knows what Killmonger did and tries to get revenge using the new combat drone. Killmonger defeats the drone and tells Tony he would not get why Killmonger wants something different to Tony. Killmonger kills Tony with a Wakandan spear and uses that to push the US military to authorize mass producing drones to attack Wakanda in retaliation. The military assumes ownership of Stark Industries for that purpose. Killmonger uses Klaue to find the border of Wakanada, then kills him to offer Klaue's body to the Wakandans. The Wakandan king T'Chaka accepts Killmonger as a family member N'Jadaka , despite daughter Shuri's concerns. T'Chaka follows Killmonger 's suggestions about isolating the US military's drone assault force from their control network by letting them into the shielded Wakandan capital. The drones seem disabled until Killmonger discreetly activates his own secondary control to restart them. He tells Shuri to blame Tony Stark's hidden components. The renewed drone advance prompts the Wakandan forces to battle them, giving Killmonger the chance to join in and demonstrate his skill and apparent bravery. T'Chaka declares Killmonger has earned the title of Black Panther along with the herb-induced powers and ceremonial uniform. Meanwhile, Pepper Potts finds Shuri in her Stark Industries office. Shuri offers evidence of Killmonger 's crimes and asks Pepper to help defeat him.

description: Thor, who never learned to be a good hero, throws an out-of-control intergalactic party on Earth.
